    <section id="how-to-find">
      <h2>How to Find the Relevant Dates</h2>
      <h3>Publication Date</h3>
      <p>Appears on the face of the published patent application. Also searchable in Google Patents and USPTO Patent Center by application number.</p>
      <h3>First Office Action Date</h3>
      <p>In <a href="https://ppair-my.uspto.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">USPTO Patent Center ↗</a>, under "Image File Wrapper," look for the first document labeled "Non-Final Rejection." The mailing date is printed on its cover.</p>
      <h3>Notice of Allowance</h3>
      <p>Also in the Image File Wrapper. If the most recent action is an NOA, the window is closed.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="edge-cases">
      <h2>Edge Cases & Nuances</h2>
      <table class="ref-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Situation</th><th>Effect on Window</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Published, no OA yet, within 6 months</td><td class="highlight">Window open. Deadline = pub date + 6 months.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>First OA issued more than 6 months after publication</td><td class="highlight">Window extended. Deadline = date of first OA.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>First OA issued within 6 months of publication</td><td>No extension. Deadline remains pub + 6 months.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>NOA issued at any point</td><td class="brittle">Window immediately closed.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Application abandoned</td><td class="brittle">Cannot file.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Continuation or divisional application</td><td>Each application has its own independent window.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>
